The LDL cholesterol levels reported in your medical documents are as follows:

1. In 2021, your LDL cholesterol level was 155 mg/dL. [Source 1: enhanced_blood_report_2021.pdf, Page 1; Source 2: enhanced_blood_report_2021.pdf, Page 1]
2. In 2022, your LDL cholesterol level was consistently reported as 130 mg/dL. [Source 4: enhanced_blood_report_2022.pdf, Page 1; Source 5: enhanced_blood_report_2022.pdf, Page 1]
3. In 2023, your LDL cholesterol level was 145 mg/dL. [Source 3: enhanced_blood_report_2023.pdf, Page 1]

These values indicate fluctuations in your LDL cholesterol levels over the years, all of which exceed the optimal range.
